(% class=&amp;#34;western&amp;#34; %)
==== Sacrificing of ritual objects fundamentally defies the logic of accumulation and the standing reserve – there are different kinds of expenditure and sacrificial expenditure is better than the forms of restricted expenditure in the status quo – we are always producing energy, so we should choose to affirm production of Heterogeneous “other” energy through inner experience and sacrifice, rather than producing more stockpiled Homogeneous energy. ====

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:1.0em;&amp;#34; %)**Stoekl ‘7**(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:0.8em;&amp;#34; %)(Allan Stoekl, “Bataille’s Peak Energy, Religion, and Postsustainability,” p. 134-137, 2007) [m leap]

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)


