The topic is not reducible to a thing – we can trace it with our knowledge but we cannot stand outside it and describe and reveal it like a picture on the wall – the archival drive to accumulate and preserve objects of knowledge only succeeds in destroying the whole experience by trying to view the topic as a thing and thus reifying and quantifying any sense of play or animality in the resolution – the Archive destroys its contents by trying to accumulate and preserving them – it annihilates the accursed share by trying to catalogue it – attempting to aesthetically encounter the topic forms a better ecological politics than aesthetic representation and accumulation – we should yield to the unthinkable which disrupts the archival drive and allows us to question the creation of a taxonomy of things
